{<content}
		<h1 class="text-center">FAQ</h1>
		<h2>How do I set this up?</h2>
		<p>
			We made that really simple for you! All you have to do is log in with twitch using the button at the top 
			right of the page, and then click the little download icon next to your name. Once the download is done 
			(it shouldn't take very long), open the file and copy and paste everything into Isaac's install folder! 
		</p>
		<p>
			<span class="text-muted">
				Typically the install location for Isaac will be at <br />
				<code>C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\SteamApps\common\The Binding of Isaac Rebirth\</code> <br />
                or<br />
				<code>C:\Users\(UserName)\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\The Binding of Isaac Rebirth\</code> <br/ >
				for most of you.
			</span>
		</p>
		<h2>Will this work on Linux/Mac?</h2>
		<p>
			Unfortunately, no. We'd love to have it working on Linux and Mac as well as Windows, but it's just not feasible 
			for us to maintain 2 more versions of the mod through future updates. It takes a lot of work!
		</p>
		<h2>Why do I have to sign in with Twitch?</h2>
		<p>
			There are a couple of reasons for this. The first is that our target audience is primarily Isaac streamers. 
			We want anyone who has a stream to have their page easy to find for viewers 
		</p>
		<p>
			There are also security reasons for this, by having you sign in with a 3rd party such as Twitch, we do not need to 
			store passwords in any way on our end, this way we can leave the security of the most important information to you 
			with a company that has a lot more money than two random guys in the Isaac community :D 
		</p>
		<h2>Will I crash?</h2>
		<p>
			Probably. Or Maybe. We haven't gotten to test it on many computers so at least while it's in Beta, you guys are the guinea pigs! 
			Make sure to contact us with any info if you are experiencing crashes.
		</p>
		<h2>Why did you set all of this up?</h2>
		<p>
			Basically, we're crazy! We both love a good challenge and this certainly has been that. Also, who wouldn't want to be able 
			to show off their current Isaac run to their friends? 
		</p>
		<h2>Take my money!</h2>
		<p>
			Ha! This isn't actually a FAQ, but we figured we could throw it in here. We've set up a donation page so 
			that anyone who actually wants to throw any money at us (You crazy person you) can. Any money sent to us goes towards our bad habits and supporting the server :D
